  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrots</strong> lengthways into long batons</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724716108911-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724716108911-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724716108911-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724716108911-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1724716108911-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and top with your <strong>thyme</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>chicken breasts </strong>over the carrots and thyme and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 25-30 minutes or until the carrots are tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>thyme summer roast chicken & roasted carrots</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724716115547-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724716115547-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724716115547-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724716115547-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1724716115547-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for an initial 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724716120659-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724716120659-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724716120659-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724716120659-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1724716120659-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>Dijon</strong> <strong>mustard</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>Dijon stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724716127120-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724716127120-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724716127120-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724716127120-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724716127120-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>mustard stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724716133344-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724716133344-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724716133344-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724716133344-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1724716133344-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>to the pot and cook for 1 min or until they're warmed through</p><p>Once warmed through, drain and return to the pot with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>potato & pea medley</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1724716138995-x200.jpg",
